Main Activities
The scope of the project involves mostly the reduction of apparent losses (customer metering inaccuracies and data handling errors) and also real losses on different levels.
 Conduct survey / assessment to determine the IWA water balance
 Calculate the global non-revenue water levels for LpWSC
 Identify, Supply and install bulk water meters at the inlet and outlet of DMAs
 Calculate the NRW in each DMA
 Identify the top 4 DMAs (2Mansa, 2Samfya) contributing to the most losses - (phase 1)
 Deploy Analytics and hardware to the 4 top DMAs (2Mansa, 2Samfya) for management – (Phase 1)
 Quantify and separate the commercial (apparent) losses from the real (physical losses)
 Reduce commercial losses by two thirds in the selected DMA
 Identify DMAs in all districts that would require meter and major pipe replacements for future projects (phase 2).
